1.title: Whale Shark
1.plot: Kamil challenges Kayne to a race a whale shark, but first needs to find one.

2.title: Sea Eagles
2.plot: Kayne and Kamil are in Queensland. Kayne's challenge is to fly using a paraglider - with the White Bellied Sea Eagle. The Sea Eagle is a master glider and a skilled hunter of large prey such as fruit bats.

3.title: Perentie
3.plot: Kayne and Kamil are off to the iconic landmark Uluru, formerly known as Ayers Rock. There, Kayne has his work cut out for him when he is challenged to find a perentie - the king of the desert and biggest lizard in Australia.

4.title: Rodeo
4.plot: Kayne tries to prove he's more than a (rodeo) clown when Kamil challenges him to jump on a bucking bull and hang on for eight seconds.

5.title: Sawfish
5.plot: Ever tried to hug a fish? Neither has Kayne, but that's his challenge as he gets up close and personal with a monster sawfish and give it a hug.

6.title: Camels
6.plot: Kayne and Kamil explore the red desert, mustering a wild camel, before Kayne has to capture its urine for a very special hair treatment.

7.title: Dugong
7.plot: Kayne and Kamil go on the hunt for the humble Dugong, in the hope of giving it a medical check up.

8.title: King Brown Snake
8.plot: From underwater to one of the world's deadliest land-dwelling creatures, this week Kayne and Kamil help to save the King Brown Snake from extinction.

9.title: Box Jellyfish
9.plot: It doesn't get deadlier than this - Kayne has to give a highly deadly Box Jellyfish a manicure.

10.title: Urban Animals
10.plot: Kamil and Kayne hit the 'big smoke' and check out some endangered urban wildlife when Bushwhacked. visits Sydney - the harbour city, home to many animals.

11.title: Tarantula
11.plot: Will Kayne be able to conquer one of his greatest fears and come face to face with a giant tarantula?

12.title: Manta Ray
12.plot: It's one thing for Kayne to take a 'selfie', but his challenge to take a happy snap with a giant Manta Ray while swimming underneath it could prove difficult.

13.title: Emu
13.plot: Kamil and Kayne travel to country NSW, where they learn that just because the emu can't fly, it doesn't mean it can't run fast.

1.title: Turtles
1.plot: Heading to the tropical beauty of Heron Island, QLD, Brandon gives Kayne his next mission - to find sea turtle hatchlings and watch them take their first swim in the ocean.

2.title: Funnel Web Spider
2.plot: Deep in the Lamington National Park rainforest in South-East Queensland Kayne faces his creepiest, crawliest mission yet - to track down one of the world's most deadly spiders - a Northern Tree-Dwelling Funnel-Web spider.

3.title: Tiger Snake
3.plot: After speeding high off the ground down a zipline in the treetops of Liffey Forest, Tasmania, Brandon sets Kayne his next mission - to find a tiger snake in the wild. Kayne and Brandon both admit this mission scares them but they head off through the honeycomb tunnels of Mole Creek Caves. The boys learn about the dreaming story of the tiger snake from Hank Norton, an Indigenous consultant, and a tiger snake skin is burnt as a blessing to the Dreamtime. Next stop on their journey is a secret snake lab where they meet herpetologist Ian Norton and his team. Ian takes ...

4.title: Cassowary
4.plot: Travelling through Cape Tribulation in far north Queensland on an amphibious truck, Brandon gives Kayne his next mission - to find a Cassowary in the wild. With only 50 birds left in the area, this won't be an easy mission.

5.title: Honey Ant
5.plot: Walking in the scorching heat through the heart of the Central Desert outside of Alice Springs, Brandon gives Kayne his next challenge - prepare a bush tucker feast to serve the Elders in the remote Aboriginal community of Papunya. The feast must include honey ants which Kayne has dug four feet underground to find.

6.title: Great White Shark
6.plot: Kayne soon discovers that riding a remote-control skateboard in the South Australian bush is the easiest part of his first mission as Brandon has set him a nerve-racking challenge - to go diving with Great White sharks! And as sharks are attracted to noise, Kayne has to beat box while under water to lure one in. Will Kayne complete the mission or will he chicken out?

8.title: Saltwater Crocodiles
8.plot: Deep inside Kakadu National Park, NT, local rangers are keen to monitor a rogue saltwater crocodile - the deadliest reptile on the planet! Brandon reckons Kayne could help them out and enlists his mate to help lure a giant croc into a cage, anaesthetise it and then attach a satellite tag to the back of its neck. In this jaw-droppingly scary mission, will Kayne rise to the challenge and get up close and personal with this deadly reptile?

9.title: Grey Nurse Shark
9.plot: Brandon and Kayne travel to Seal Rocks, off the northern coast of NSW, where Brandon gives Kayne his next mission - to swim with Grey Nurse Sharks and take a photo of one. Seal Rocks is renowned for having one of the last colonies of endangered Grey Nurse Sharks - there's only about 400 left in the wild.

11.title: Melbourne
11.plot: High above Melbourne doing 360 degree spins in WWII fighter planes, Kayne introduces Brandon to his home turf. During this episode the tables are turned as Kayne sets Brandon a mission - being involved in the rescue of three different animals which live in the big city.

13.title: Cattle Muster
13.plot: On the farm, stockman Justin Hill puts the boys through their paces as they clean stables, learn to sheer sheep, test cows for pregnancy and show off their horse riding skills.

-1.title: Arafura File Snake
-1.plot: Brandon and Kayne are headed to Arnhem Land, Northern Territory, for Kayne's final mission - he must catch, cook and eat an Arafura File Snake. The Arafura File Snake is a rare delicacy in the area, and lives in water - the same water that crocodiles live in!

imdb.plot outline: Join mates Brandon Walters (Australia) and ABC3's Kayne Tremills on a wild journey as they trek throughout Australia on some seriously weird and sometimes deadly wildlife missions in this action-packed, adrenalin-pumping adventure series. From chasing down dangerous spiders, killer sharks and venomous snakes, as well as friendly penguins and lovable turtles, the boys are constantly kept on their toes as Brandon sets Kayne amazing missions to complete during each episode.
imdb.title: Bushwhacked!
plot: _Bushwhacked!_ (qv) is a high-energy, adrenalin-fueled race around Australia in search of weird, wacky and endangered species!
